    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/677.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Jefferson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 10. Please report reductions proposed in salaries to
                    Americans.</p>
                <p>While it is unjust as well as unreasonable to ask for excessive salaries for
                    American officials, still it must be remembered that no one is likely to go to
                    Nicaragua from this country unless he could make more there than here.
                    Interruption of business, absence from home and discomforts in foreign country
                    must all be taken into consideration. This Department glad to assist in making
                    reasonable reductions, but could not advise such reductions as would make it
                    impossible to secure the competent and efficient men needed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
